body.description: Slice, dice, and prep with this set of two paring knives from Iron Chef Geoffrey Zakarian and the product innovators at Dash. This set includes one Serrated Paring Knife, perfect for chopping small vegetables, and one Smooth Paring Knife, ideal for prepping delicate cuts of meat. Both knives are made with high-quality German steel for a durable finish that resists corrosion and chipping, bringing you the convenience of being dishwasher safe. The full-tang blades with triple rivet handles provide maximum strength, balance and durability. All Zakarian by Dash cutlery is backed by a 1 year limited warranty and US based customer support. Make precision cuts and elevate your cooking from start to finish!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great paring knifes. Super sharp.
reviews.reviewText: These are very nice they are not to hefty but weightier than others. Nice size handle to grip with love that they are a little bigger and feel more substantial in your hand. It’s nice to have a straight edge and serrated. Good value for your $$$. I would expect nothing less from GZ.Beware: these are very very sharp and you have probably been using dull blades so keep your fingers tucked in.

reviews.reviewText: I didn't know I needed these knives till they arrived. Absolute dream to cut fruits and Vegetables with. Fits my hand perfectly. Cutting up these items is a dream now. Super sharp too!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not holding an edge
reviews.reviewText: The knives look and feel good, have a nice weight and good balance. The blades have a confidence instilling height and thickness, are full tang, and a secured with three rivets to the handle. The seated knife is a nice tomato slicer. The straight blade came very sharp out of the box became dull during its first use prepping, cutting bell peppers, onions, and zucchinis on a wooden board. Honing didn't help but a quick 300-1000-6000 whetstone treatment got it back to great sharpness. I then cored some jalapenos, cut some corn of the ear, and diced onions, but the blade was already dull when it came to the tomatoes. I should have invested more money and not be intrigued by the knives' looks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Use these knives every day
reviews.reviewText: I cannot believe how amazing these knives are. I love the weight of them. The size is perfect for my small hands. So comfortable to use and they are razor sharp. Slice threw any fruit or vegetable with no effort at all. I can easily peel squash with this. I use the smooth bladed one all the time. Having a small, serrated knife is a game changer for me. It comes in handy. I keep them on a magnetic strip. My go-to knives. The quality is superb. I expect these to last a ling, long time. I am so delighted with this knife set.
